<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>DaysOfTranquility: WikiOptions</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY ALINK="#00CC00" LINK="#3C914D" VLINK="#005500" BGCOLOR="#CCCC99"><H1><a href="wiki.pl?HomePage"><img src="/forums/DoT_Sword.jpg" alt="[Home]" border=0 align="right"></a><a href="wiki.pl?search=WikiOptions">WikiOptions</a></H1><a href="wiki.pl?HomePage">HomePage</a> | <a href="wiki.pl?RecentChanges">RecentChanges</a> | <a href="wiki.pl?action=editprefs">Preferences</a> | 
<hr><b>No diff available--this is the first major revision.</b>
(no other diffs)<hr>The DaysOfTranquility wiki currently uses the <a href="http://www.usemod.com/cgi-bin/wiki.pl?UseModWiki">UseMod:UseModWiki</a> server software, which includes many options for the <a href="wiki.pl?RecentChanges">RecentChanges</a> page.  Here are some examples:
<p>
<UL>
<li> Display minor edits: <a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=rc&showedit=1">DaysOfTranquility:action=rc&amp;showedit=1</a>
<li> List changes in last 12 hours: <a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=rc&days=0.5">DaysOfTranquility:action=rc&amp;days=0.5</a>
<li> List 3 days of changes: <a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=rc&days=3">DaysOfTranquility:action=rc&amp;days=3</a>
<li> List <strong>all</strong> changes in the last 24 hours: <a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=rc&days=1&all=1&showedit=1">DaysOfTranquility:action=rc&amp;days=1&amp;all=1&amp;showedit=1</a>
<li> List all changes except minor edits: <a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=rc&all=1&showedit=0">DaysOfTranquility:action=rc&amp;all=1&amp;showedit=0</a>
<li> List <strong>only</strong> minor edits: <a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=rc&all=1&showedit=2">DaysOfTranquility:action=rc&amp;all=1&amp;showedit=2</a>
<li> List oldest items first: <a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=rc&newtop=0">DaysOfTranquility:action=rc&amp;newtop=0</a>
</UL>
<p>
For a full index of all pages: <a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=index">DaysOfTranquility:action=index</a>
<hr>
The LinkDatabase<a href="wiki.pl?action=edit&id=LinkDatabase">?</a> feature gives a list of all page-links in the local wiki. The first link on each line is to the page being searched, and the following links are those that were found on that page.
Samples: [Note that all the options can be combined]
<p>
<p>
<UL>
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links">DaysOfTranquility:action=links</a> (plain list)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&editlink=1">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;editlink=1</a> (non-existant pages include the "?" edit-link)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&empty=1">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;empty=1</a> (list "empty" pages (without any links of the requested type))
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&names=0">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;names=0</a> (just the links, no page names)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&unique=0">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;unique=0</a> (every instance of the link, not just the first one per page)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&unique=2">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;unique=2</a> (only list each link one time (do not repeat it on later pages))
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&sort=0">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;sort=0</a> (links in the order they appear on the page)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&exists=0">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;exists=0</a> (only links to non-existant pages)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&exists=1">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;exists=1</a> (only links to existing pages)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&url=1">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;url=1</a> (also include URL links)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&url=2">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;url=2</a> (*only* include URL links)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&inter=1">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;inter=1</a> (also include InterWiki<a href="wiki.pl?action=edit&id=InterWiki">?</a> links)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&inter=2">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;inter=2</a> (*only* include InterWiki<a href="wiki.pl?action=edit&id=InterWiki">?</a> links)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&inter=2&search=UseMod">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;inter=2&amp;search=UseMod</a>: (Search for InterWiki<a href="wiki.pl?action=edit&id=InterWiki">?</a> links to UseMod<a href="wiki.pl?action=edit&id=UseMod">?</a>?)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&url=2&search=crit.org">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;url=2&amp;search=crit.org</a> (Search for URL links mentioning crit.org)
<li><a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=links&names=0&unique=2&exists=0">DaysOfTranquility:action=links&amp;names=0&amp;unique=2&amp;exists=0</a> (show all non-existant (wanted) links, showing each link only once)
</UL>
<p>
Notes:
<UL>
<li>All URLs and InterWiki<a href="wiki.pl?action=edit&id=InterWiki">?</a> links are considered non-existant. (It would be rather expensive to check them.)
<li>The setting empty=0 may leave blank lines if names=0 is also set.
</UL>
<hr>
The LinkDatabase<a href="wiki.pl?action=edit&id=LinkDatabase">?</a> feature currently rescans the entire database every time it is used, so it is slow and CPU-intensive.  Eventually the code will store the results and reuse them.
<hr>
These options (and many others like one's UserName<a href="wiki.pl?action=edit&id=UserName">?</a> and TimeZone<a href="wiki.pl?action=edit&id=TimeZone">?</a>) can also be set using <a href="http://www.twinked.com/guilds/DaysOfTranquility/wiki/wiki.pl?action=editprefs">[Preferences]</a>.
<p>
<em>Question: are there more options than this with the new versions of UseModWiki<a href="wiki.pl?action=edit&id=UseModWiki">?</a>?</em>
